dcterms:description: The dataset for England specifically consists of 129 regions for a total of 61 days. Each region is represented as a node in the graph and each edge represents the movement of people from one region to another. Edge attributes represent the number of movements between the two regions.
dcterms:title: EnglandCovid Dataset

dcterms:description: The dataset consists of 30 days of edits made by users on Wiki pages after selecting the 1000 most edited pages and users who have edited at least 5 pages resulting in a total of 8227 users. The total number of nodes is 9227 (8227 users and 1000 pages), and the total number of interactions or edges occurring over time is 157,474.
dcterms:title: Wikipedia Dataset
